{
  "texts": [
    "The Essence of Aspect Term Extraction (ATE) along with Opinion Term Extraction (OTE) based on BanglaBERT filters out improper spans and protects authentic aspect-opinion elements.",
    "D. Aspect-Opinion MatchingThe extraction process utilizes graph-based methods with semantic similarity algorithms to accuracy match between detected aspect terms and opinion phrases.",
    "A proper system is established for matching aspects and opinions in this process to accurately validate their relationships.",
    "E. Sentiment ClassificationThe sentiment classification process combines XGBoost with BanglaBERT through an ensemble model design for better accuracy results.",
    "The combined model uses BanglaBERT context understanding with XGBoost boosting capabilities to achieve superior classification results.The model evaluation process used accuracy alongside precision recall and F1-score along with accuracy to perform complete model performance assessment through five-fold cross-validation testing for generalization.The data analysis revealed main classification obstacles were related to sarcastic statements and unclear wordings and combinations of positive and negative feelings."
  ]
}